The paper deals with the computational complexity of solving systems of linear equations over F_2, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The problem of computing sparse solutions to these systems is related to topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the implications of the hardness results for learning sparse parities, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
